Author-Name:  P. Raghavendra Rau 
Author-Name:  Aris Stouraitis 
Title: Helping Hand or Grabbing Hand? Central vs. Local Government Shareholders in Chinese Listed Firms 
Abstract:
 We analyze related party transactions between Chinese publicly listed
 firms and their state-owned shareholders to examine whether companies
 benefit or lose from the presence of government shareholders and
 politically connected directors. Minority shareholders seem to be
 expropriated in firms controlled by local governments, firms with a large
 proportion of local government directors on their board, firms without
 central government directors, and firms in provinces where local
 government bureaucrats are less likely to be prosecuted for corruption. In
 contrast, firms controlled by the central government (or having central
 government affiliated directors), benefit in related party transactions
 with their government parents. Copyright 2010, Oxford University Press.
