Author-Name:  Alessandro Beber 
Author-Name:  Michael W. Brandt 
Title: Resolving Macroeconomic Uncertainty in Stock and Bond Markets 
Abstract:
 We establish an empirical link between the ex-ante uncertainty about
 macroeconomic fundamentals and the ex-post resolution of this uncertainty
 in financial markets. We measure macroeconomic uncertainty using prices of
 economic derivatives and relate this measure to changes in implied
 volatilities of stock and bond options when the economic data is released.
 Higher macroeconomic uncertainty is associated with greater reduction in
 implied volatilities following the news release. It is also associated
 with increased volume and decreased open interest in option markets after
 the release, consistent with market participants using financial options
 to hedge or speculate on macroeconomic news. Copyright 2009, Oxford University Press.
