Author-Name:  Fernando Restoy
Author-Name:  Philippe Weil 
Title: Approximate Equilibrium Asset Prices 
Abstract:
 Arguing that total consumer wealth is unobservable, we invert the
 (approximate) consumption function to reconstruct, in a world with
 Kreps-Porteus generalized isoelastic preferences, (i) the wealth that
 supports the agents' observed consumption as an optimal outcome and (ii)
 the rate of return on the consumers' wealth portfolio. This allows us to
 (approximately) price assets solely as a function of their payoffs and of
 consumption--in both homoskedastic or heteroskedastic environments. We
 compare implied equilibrium returns on the wealth portfolio to observed
 stock market returns and gauge whether the stock market is a good proxy
 for unobserved aggregate wealth. Copyright 2011, Oxford University Press.
