Title: A Dynamic Analysis of Growth via Acquisition 
Abstract:
 Firms can grow through internal investment or through acquisition. While
 internal growth takes time, an acquisition provides cash flows
 immediately. The opportunity to grow internally affects the price of an
 acquisition as it is a fall-back option for the acquirer should
 negotiations break down. Assuming investors do not have full information
 about the time a firm requires to grow internally, acquirers earn positive
 returns before the announcement of an acquisition, and there are negative
 stock price reactions to acquisition announcements. This research provides
 predictions about how pre-announcement price run-up and negative
 announcement returns relate to integration costs and synergies from
 acquisition. Copyright 2008, Oxford University Press.
