Author-Name:  Yaron Leitner
Title: Inducing Agents to Report Hidden Trades: A Theory of an Intermediary 
Abstract:
 When contracts are unobserved (and nonexclusive), agents can promise the
 same asset to multiple counterparties and subsequently default. I show
 that a central mechanism can extract all relevant information about
 contracts that agents enter by inducing them to report one another. The
 mechanism sets position limits and reveals the names of agents who hit the
 limits according to (voluntary) reports from their counterparties. This
 holds even if sending reports is costly and even if agents can collude. In
 some cases, an agent's position limit must be nonbinding in equilibrium.
 The mechanism has some features of a clearinghouse. Copyright 2012, Oxford University Press.
