Author-Name:  Mike Burkart 
Author-Name:  Samuel Lee 
Title: One Share - One Vote: the Theory 
Abstract:
 The theoretical literature on security-voting structure can be organized
 around three questions: What impact do nonvoting shares have on takeover
 outcomes? How does disproportional voting power affect the incentives of
 blockholders? What are the repercussions of mandating one share - one vote
 for firms' financing and ownership choices? Overall, the costs and
 benefits of separating cash flow and votes reflect the fundamental
 governance trade off between disempowering blockholders and empowering
 managers. It is therefore an open question whether mandating one share -
 one vote would improve the quality of corporate governance, notably in
 systems that so far relied on active owners. Copyright 2008, Oxford University Press.
