 effective spreads of securities traded at the Berlin Stock Exchange in
 1880, 1890, 1900 and 1910. Several extensions of the Roll measure are
 applied. We find surprisingly tight effective spreads for the historical
 data, comparable with similar measures of the MDAX and DAX at the end of
 the 20th century.		      Copyright Oxford University Press Science+Business Media, LLC 2006
