Author-Name:  Danling Jiang 
Author-Name:  David R. Peterson 
Title: Gambling Preference and the New Year Effect of Assets with Lottery Features 
Abstract:
 This paper shows that a New Year's gambling preference of individual
 investors impacts prices and returns of assets with lottery features.
 January call options, especially the out-of-the-money calls, have higher
 retail demand and are the most expensive and actively traded. Lottery-type
 stocks outperform their counterparts in January but tend to underperform
 in other months. Retail sentiment is more bullish in lottery-type stocks
 in January than in other months. Furthermore, lottery-type Chinese stocks
 outperform in the Chinese New Year's Month but not in January. This New
 Year effect provides new insights into the broad phenomena related to the
 January effect. Copyright 2011, Oxford University Press.
