Title: Cash Breeds Success: The Role of Financing Constraints in Patent Races 
Abstract:
 This paper studies the impact of financing constraints in patent races. We
 develop a model of optimal contracting where firms finance their R&D
 expenditures with an investor who cannot verify their effort. In
 equilibrium, firms are more likely to win the more cash and assets they
 hold prior to the race, and the less cash and assets their rivals hold
 prior to the race. Evidence from US pharmaceutical patents awarded between
 1975 and 1999 supports our theoretical predictions. Copyright 2010, Oxford University Press.
