Author-Name:  Ben Jacobsen 
Title: Are Monthly Seasonals Real? A Three Century Perspective 
Abstract:
 Over 300 years of UK stock returns reveal that well-known monthly
 seasonals are sample specific. For instance, the January effect only
 emerges around 1830. Most months have had their 50 years of fame, showing
 the importance of long time series to safeguard against sample selection
 bias, noise, and data snooping. The overall conclusion is that monthly
 seasonals might simply be in the eye of the beholder. Copyright 2013, Oxford University Press.
