Author-Name:  Rodolfo Martell 
Title: Understanding Common Factors in Domestic and International Bond Spreads 
Abstract:
 I study the determinants of changes in credit spreads for U.S. dollar
 denominated domestic and foreign sovereign bonds using fundamentals
 specified by structural models to separate spreads into their credit and
 non-credit components. I find that the non-default portions of spreads
 have a component that is common for each type of debt. Further, using a
 vector autoregressive model, I find that domestic spreads are related to
 the lagged component of sovereign spreads. I also find that some proxies
 for liquidity are related to the common components, suggesting a
 liquidity-based explanation for the common component not identified by
 previous research. Copyright 2008, Oxford University Press.
