Author-Name:  Marco Del Negro 
Title: Firm-Level Evidence on International Stock Market Comovement 
Abstract:
 We explore the link between international stock market comovement and the
 extent to which firms operate globally. Using stock returns and balance
 sheet data for companies in 20 countries, we estimate a factor model that
 decomposes stock returns into global, country- and industry-specific
 shocks. We find a large and statistically significant link for global
 shocks. A firm raising its international sales by 10 percent raises the
 exposure of its stock return to global shocks by two percent. This link
 has grown stronger over time since the mid-1980s. We find no similarly
 robust link between international sales and exposure to country-specific
 shocks. Copyright 2006, Oxford University Press.
